The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Bachchan better 

 Mumbai, Dec. 4 (PTI): Security at Lilavati Hospital has been tightened after a TV reporter allegedly barged into the intensive care unit to interview Amitabh Bachchan, sources said today.

 Two private guards, suspected to have let the woman reporter in yesterday after she allegedly pretended to be a patient, have been removed from duty.

 Showing signs of improvement after his surgery, Amitabh today took a stroll in the ICU. 

 In a letter to the superstar, Prime Minister Manmohan Singh has wished him speedy recovery.




